      "date": "2020-05-24 06:25:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I know the trailing \"*/\" is needed on a separate line, but is the leading \"/*\" required by checkpatch? I'd prefer we didn't add this decoration if it isn't needed, as it just consumes an extra line on the screen for little benefit.  If checkpatch _does_ complain about it, then I guess I'll accept it.\n\nAndreas, got it. Leading '/*' is not mandatory. Will not add it in further patches.",
